                    enclose the email address in quotes, such as "<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="/Users/user/Documents/dev/python/DITA/topics-dita/205860137-Change-alerts-and-workflows.dita" xtrc="b:6;149:70">John-L-Hughes@gmail.com".</b>
                
         </li>
                
         <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="/Users/user/Documents/dev/python/DITA/topics-dita/205860137-Change-alerts-and-workflows.dita" xtrc="li:17;153:14">You can specify that the email address be taken from a field in the record that is being updated. For example, when a new order is captured, you may wish to send email to the customer who
                    created the order. You can do this by entering an expression specifying the field name containing the customer's email address. For example, if there is a field called "CustomerEmail"
                    in the updated record, you can specify <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="/Users/user/Documents/dev/python/DITA/topics-dita/205860137-Change-alerts-and-workflows.dita" xtrc="b:7;155:63">[CustomerEmail]</b> in the email address list.
                </li>
                
