            <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="/Users/user/Documents/dev/python/DITA/topics-dita/205860137-Change-alerts-and-workflows.dita" xtrc="b:22;201:16">Email body: </b>May contain template variables. Use this field when you have a simple email body.
                </li>
                
         <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="/Users/user/Documents/dev/python/DITA/topics-dita/205860137-Change-alerts-and-workflows.dita" xtrc="li:24;204:14">
                    
            <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="/Users/user/Documents/dev/python/DITA/topics-dita/205860137-Change-alerts-and-workflows.dita" xtrc="b:23;206:16">Body template: </b>For more complex workflow emails, you can specify a Google doc that may contain text, images, and placeholders (see next section about placeholders). After
                    the placeholders are replaced the resulting document becomes the email body. Use this field when you have a more complex email body. When a Body template is present, it is used in lieu of
                    the €œEmail body€.
